1ï¸âƒ£ Opposite Direction (Left & Right)

Start from both ends

Used in sorted arrays

Example:

Two Sum II

Container With Most Water

2ï¸âƒ£ Same Direction (Slow & Fast)

Both start from beginning

Fast explores, slow processes

Example:

Remove duplicates

Move zeroes

3ï¸âƒ£ Fast & Slow Pointer

Fast moves faster than slow

Used for cycles / filtering

Example:

Linked List Cycle

Remove nth node

4ï¸âƒ£ Sliding Window (Advanced Two Pointer)

Window expands and shrinks

Used for subarray problems

Example:

Longest substring

Max sum subarray

